        "heading": "It started with one dark hallway",
        "text": "<p>Meave London began with a problem its founder, Meave Sinclair, could not stop thinking about. As an interior stylist in London, she spent her days making rooms feel calm and finished, only to watch them undone by harsh, badly placed lighting that needed an electrician to fix.</p><p>During a long winter at home she sketched a different kind of light: a wall sconce with the warmth and proportions of a designer piece, but completely wireless. No drilling, no rewiring, no permission from a landlord. The first brass prototype went up in her own hallway in 2021, and within weeks friends and clients were asking where to buy one.</p><p>So she made more. Today Meave London designs warm, wireless wall lights, shades and furniture accents for people who want a styled, finished home without the renovation.</p>",
